The paper discusses a new training algorithm for deep learning models that exploit structured input via complex and instance-dependent control flow, which is difficult to accelerate using existing algorithms and hardware that typically rely on minibatching. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
